courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon the completion of the course, students are expected to be able to:
1. articulate an overview of sociology as a discipline;
2. identify and explain major sociological concepts and theories;
3. identify and explain basic sociological research methods;
4. analyze social phenomenon from a sociological perspective;
5. reflect on one’s values and experiences in life

After completing the course, the students should be able to:
1 gain an intellectual understanding of the nature and possible causes of criminal and deviant behaviors;
2 capture an overview of sociological theories on crime and deviance;
3 identify and critically evaluate certain commonly-held views regarding crime and deviance; and
4 analyze the issues of crime and deviance in Hong Kong from various sociological perspectives.

